message: It's a great day in Washington for the swearing in ceremony of the 115th Congress of the United States of America. Joining us are my wife Sheila and two of our children, Jackson and Morgan. #MS01
It was great to see Steve Holloway, Michelle, Harli and Rider Sesser from Columbus. They were here for a tour of the Capitol. #MS01
The 115th Congress convenes. Please read my newsletter to learn more. #MS01  ↓
It is an honor to serve on the House Armed Services Committee and the House Committee on Agriculture. Please read my news release. #MS01  ↓
It is an honor to serve on the House Armed Services Committee, the House Agriculture Committee and the House Small Business Committee. Please read my newsletter to learn more. #MS01 ↓

Sue Morrison from Union County can't wait for next Friday, "I'm so excited. I haven't slept. It's an awesome opportunity!" She and a friend will be in DC to watch President-elect Donald J. Trump take the oath of office. Our team is excited for her and others who received tickets to witness this historic event. #MS01
Remembering the words of civil rights leader Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. His contributions will never be forgotten.

Jacob and Jane Claire Abel are looking forward to their trip to watch President-elect Donald J. Trump take the oath of office The DeSoto County couple received tickets through our office to the inauguration ceremony. Jane says this is an exciting opportunity for she and her husband, a military veteran. "We were very interested in this historic election. We decided to contact Rep. Kelly's office to see if we could get tickets. We did!" Our team was glad to assist them. #MS01
It is an honor to serve in a leadership role for the House Small Business Committee. #MS01

Trey and Lara Bowman from Choctaw County will be in DC to watch President-elect Donald J. Trump take the oath of office. "This was an election that stood out. Our plan to attend the ceremony is a special something that you need to do," Lara said. Trey works in the agriculture industry. Lara is The Enterprise of Mississippi Executive Director which is the economic development association for Webster and Choctaw Counties. Both say they are optimistic about the economy because the new president is pro-business. #MS01

Our DC office will be open today, January 19th for inauguration ticket pick-up from 9:00 a.m - 6:00 p.m. Whether or not you received tickets from our office, if you are in town for inauguration, please stop by! #MS01

Jeanette Hollowell from DeSoto County will be in DC to watch President-elect Donald J. Trump take the oath of office. "I started trying to get tickets the minute the election was over," Jeanette said. "I was determined to go and Rep. Kelly made it possible." Jeanette, a realtor, also attended the inauguration ceremonies for President George H.W. Bush. "We had a seat below the podium that day. I will never forget it!" #MS01

President Donald Trump has signed a federal disaster declaration that will help south Mississippi recover from severe weather Jan. 20-21. We pray for their recovery from these storms which claimed lives and damaged or destroyed property. Please read the letter the Mississippi congressional delegation sent to President Trump. #MS01  ↓

We pray for the full recovery of two DeSoto County Sheriff's Department deputies who were shot in the line of duty last night. Patrol Sgt. Hunter Garrett and K9 Deputy Brandon Lee Hutchens are to be commended for their sacrifice trying to keep others safe. #MS01

It was good to see Vice President Mike Pence who, along with President Donald J. Trump , joined us for the 2017 Republican Congressional Retreat in Philadelphia this week. I am excited about the direction we are headed. It is an honor to be your voice in Washington. #MS01

Today, hundreds of thousands of Americans are taking part in the March for Life. This peaceful protest and march is a reminder to the world that we must protect the unborn. This week, the House passed with my support H.R. 7, the No Taxpayer Funding for Abortion Act. No taxpayer should be forced to fund abortion. It is the goal of the 115th Congress to defend life. #MS01
Our country has the opportunity to get back on the right path. Please read my newsletter to learn more. #MS01  ↓

President Trump is keeping his promise to nominate a conservative, well-respected judge to the United States Supreme Court. Judge Neil M. Gorsuch is a proven leader who has demonstrated a fair and accurate record for interpreting the law and a profound respect for our Constitution. In 2006, he was confirmed by the U.S. Senate to the Colorado-based U.S. Court of Appeals without opposition. I am hopeful that this highly respected jurist receives a swift and fair confirmation process. #MS01

It was good to spend time with National Federation of the Blind Mississippi Chapter President Sam Gleese. He visited our DC office with Ollie Lester of Columbus, Candice Chapman and Angel Darden. #MS01

Tomorrow, the House Small Business Committee meets for a hearing on the healthcare law. We will examine how Republican alternatives will improve access and affordability for Americans nationwide. You can watch it live at 10 a.m. CST and 11 a.m. EST. #MS01  ↓

The House Armed Services Committee hearing will be held at 9 a.m. CST this morning. The Full Committee will meet in open session to receive testimony about the readiness of our military. Click on the link below to watch it live. #MS01   ↓

As a member of the House Armed Services Committee, it remains a top priority to make sure our military men and women, including Columbus Air Force Base Airmen, have the equipment and training they need to keep our nation safe. At "The State of the Military" hearing this morning, our military leaders made it clear we have to be prepared to fight any adversary. I will work to make sure our armed forces have the necessary funds to restore readiness capabilities. #MS01

In March, 1942, Navy Construction Battalion personnel were officially named Seabees by the U.S. Navy. Their motto is "We build, we fight". Their mission to build and maintain critical military infrastructure for the Navy and U.S. Marine Corps, while defending our nation, continues to this day. It is an honor to recognize their 75th anniversary. #MS01

Each spring, the U.S. House of Representatives sponsor the nationwide Congressional Art Competition. The winner of the First District competition will have their artwork displayed with other contest winners at the U.S. Capitol for one year. All high school students are encouraged to submit their artwork and entry forms to the district office in Tupelo or Corinth. For more information, call Melinda Whited at (662) 687-1525. #MS01

Small Business operators fuel Mississippi's economy, employing thousands of our citizens. Show your support for small business operators this Saturday. Go shopping! #MS01

This Thanksgiving I led a bipartisan delegation to visit soldiers, sailors, airmen, and Marines stationed in locations across Poland, Qatar, Uzbekistan, Afghanistan, and Ireland. We talked with military leaders and troops on the ground. We also met with national defense leaders to better understand the posture and readiness of U.S. forces in these locations. Ultimately, this trip allowed me and my congressional colleagues to share in person our appreciation of their service and to help serve the Thanksgiving meal to our military men and women in Afghanistan. During this holiday season, let us all remember service members at home and abroad who are working to preserve our freedoms during these uncertain times across the world. #MS01

As a member of the House Armed Services Committee Republicans, it was an honor to join my colleagues including HASC Chairman Mac Thornberry and Speaker Paul Ryan for the signing of the 2018 National Defense Authorization Act (NDAA). This legislation sets the budget for national defense spending, provides for our troops, and establishes national defense policy. This demonstrates our commitment to military men and women who must have the tools they need to protect America at home and abroad. We have more work to do to rebuild our nation's defense readiness capabilities. This is a step in the right direction. #MS01

Today I spoke at the 21st National Guard Association of the United States (NGAUS) Industry Day at the National Guard Memorial in Washington, D.C. I stressed the importance of fully funding our military and not hamstringing our service members with more continuing resolutions. This year more soldiers, sailors, airmen, and Marines have died in training accidents with worn out equipment than in combat against the enemies of America. Our industry partners are ready to deliver new, upgraded, or repaired equipment to the Department of Defense but can only do so if they have reliable funding. As your representative, I will continue to work to get the proper weapons and equipment to our Department of Defense.  #MS01
As a member of the Mississippi National Guard for 32 years, it is an honor and a privilege to serve our nation. #NationalGuardbirthday #MS01
